cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses training neural networks for image classification tasks, specifically for handwritten digit recognition and NORB image database. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these, cs.NE is the most likely category as the paper focuses on training neural networks using the Extreme Learning Machine algorithm. The other categories are also likely as they are related to image classification and machine learning.
